There is hereby established in the Department of Law the Child Support Enforcement Commission which shall consist of nine (9) members as prescribed below:
The Attorney General, or a designee, who shall also serve as chairman;
The secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services, or his or her designee, who shall also serve as vice chairman;
The director of the Administrative Office of the Courts, or his or her designee;
The commissioner, or his or her designee, of the Department for Income Support within the Cabinet for Health and Family Services; and
The remaining five (5) members shall be appointed by the Governor for terms of four (4) years, except that the initial appointments shall be made in the following manner: One (1) member for two (2) years, two (2) members for three (3) years, and two (2) members for four (4) years. Each member shall serve until a successor is named and any appointment, due to vacancy, shall be for the unexpired term. The remaining five (5) members shall be appointed in the following manner: three (3) members from a list of nine (9) nominees submitted by the Kentucky County Attorney Association, with one (1) of the three members representing either a first class or urban-county government, and two (2) citizen-at-large members.

The commission shall have the following responsibilities:
Advise the Governor on any issue related to the child-support program;
Advise the Cabinet for Health and Family Services on any issue related to the child-support program;
Advise the Department of Law on any issue related to the child-support program;
Advise the Administrative Office of the Courts on any issue related to the child-support program;
Provide a regular forum for all parties involved in the child-support program to address any aspect of the administrative or judicial process;
Develop and prepare reports and recommendations related to administrative procedures, prosecution, judicial procedures, state or federal legislation; or any other matters which might improve program effectiveness and efficiency; and
Initiate recommendations to facilitate interaction between local officials and the cabinet.
